          <title>Chief Complaint</title>
          <text>Patient presented with acute chest pain radiating to the left arm, diaphoresis, and shortness of breath. Onset 2 hours prior to arrival. EKG on arrival showed ST-elevation in leads II, III, aVF consistent with inferior STEMI.</text>
