          <title>Hospital Course</title>
          <text>Patient was taken emergently to the cardiac catheterization laboratory. Coronary angiography revealed a 100% occlusion of the right coronary artery. Successful primary PCI was performed with placement of a drug-eluting stent. Post-procedure troponin peaked at 48.2 ng/mL. Patient remained hemodynamically stable throughout. Echocardiogram on day 2 showed EF of 45% with inferior wall hypokinesis. Patient was ambulating without symptoms by day 3. Discharged on aspirin, clopidogrel, metoprolol, atorvastatin, and lisinopril.</text>
        </section>
